Page 42. Duplicate of Object 63.7, which is captioned "Mohammadan initiation ceremony - girls, Zanzibar". -- Page 47. British consulate, Zanzibar. (General Note)

The album includes uncaptioned photographs of German military officers, Zanzibari officials, and local people, both in posed and casual photographs. The photographs depict a variety of social scenes at different locales, including the Sultan's palace. All captions have been supplied for the inventory.

The Humphrey Winterton Collection of East African Photographs: 1860-1960

The collection depicts the breadth of African experience; documents African life; European life in Africa in all its manifestations; and the African landscape, in particular as it changed over time. Included are photographs showing the building of East Africa’s railways, the growth of its urban centers and the development of European colonial administration. There are outstanding examples of portraiture. The collection provides an unsurpassed resource for the study of the history of photography in East Africa.
